OL,3,CTwo men jailed after unprecedented
OL,4,Cmulti-million pound fraud case
OL,6,FThe crimes were only revealed after Mr
OL,7,FJeanne had retired and his successor
OL,8,Fstarted to realise that money had gone
OL,9,Fmissing.
OL,11,FIn sentencing the two men,
OL,12,FCommissioner Sir John Saunders said
OL,13,F"this was an offence of the greatest
OL,14,Fgravity".
OL,16,FReferring to Mr Jeanne, he added: "It
OL,17,Fwas difficult to contemplate a more
OL,18,Fserious break of trust."
